### Football Manager API — request playbook
### Run these requests top-to-bottom. Each block stores ids into variables that
### later requests reuse, so you can walk through a complete scenario without
### copy-pasting ids by hand.
###
### Works in IntelliJ's built-in HTTP Client and in VS Code's "REST Client"
### extension. Press the "Run" gutter icon next to each request, or run all.

@host = http://localhost:8080


# =============================================================================
# 1. CREATE TEAMS
# =============================================================================

### Create FC Tecnocampus
POST {{host}}/teams
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "FC Tecnocampus",
  "city": "Mataró"
}

> {%
client.global.set("teamId", response.body.id);
%}

### Create a rival team — Real Mataró
POST {{host}}/teams
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Real Mataró",
  "city": "Mataró"
}

> {%
client.global.set("rivalTeamId", response.body.id);
%}

### List all teams
GET {{host}}/teams

### Get a specific team (includes player roster)
GET {{host}}/teams/{{teamId}}

### League table (sorted by points → goalDifference → goalsFor)
GET {{host}}/teams/league-table


# =============================================================================
# 2. CREATE PLAYERS (free agents)
# =============================================================================

### Create a forward
POST {{host}}/players
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Lamine Yamal",
  "position": "FWD",
  "skillLevel": 88
}

> {%
client.global.set("forwardId", response.body.id);
%}

### Create a midfielder
POST {{host}}/players
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Pedri",
  "position": "MID",
  "skillLevel": 85
}

> {%
client.global.set("midId", response.body.id);
%}

### Create a defender
POST {{host}}/players
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Iñigo Martínez",
  "position": "DEF",
  "skillLevel": 78
}

> {%
client.global.set("defId", response.body.id);
%}

### Create a goalkeeper for the rival team
POST {{host}}/players
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Ter Stegen",
  "position": "GK",
  "skillLevel": 90
}

> {%
client.global.set("rivalGkId", response.body.id);
%}

### Create a forward for the rival team
POST {{host}}/players
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Lewandowski",
  "position": "FWD",
  "skillLevel": 92
}

> {%
client.global.set("rivalFwdId", response.body.id);
%}

### List all players
GET {{host}}/players

### Filter players by position
GET {{host}}/players?position=FWD

### Filter players by status
GET {{host}}/players?status=FREE_AGENT

### Get a specific player
GET {{host}}/players/{{forwardId}}

### Update a player (only name and skillLevel may change; position is fixed)
PUT {{host}}/players/{{forwardId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Lamine Yamal Nasraoui",
  "skillLevel": 90
}


# =============================================================================
# 3. SIGN PLAYERS (cost = skillLevel × 2; deducts from team budget)
# =============================================================================

### Sign forward to FC Tecnocampus
POST {{host}}/teams/{{teamId}}/sign/{{forwardId}}

### Sign midfielder to FC Tecnocampus
POST {{host}}/teams/{{teamId}}/sign/{{midId}}

### Sign defender to FC Tecnocampus
POST {{host}}/teams/{{teamId}}/sign/{{defId}}

### Sign goalkeeper to Real Mataró
POST {{host}}/teams/{{rivalTeamId}}/sign/{{rivalGkId}}

### Sign forward to Real Mataró
POST {{host}}/teams/{{rivalTeamId}}/sign/{{rivalFwdId}}


# =============================================================================
# 4. PLAY MATCHES
# =============================================================================

### Play a match — FC Tecnocampus (home) vs Real Mataró (away)
POST {{host}}/matches
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "homeTeamId": "{{teamId}}",
  "awayTeamId": "{{rivalTeamId}}"
}

> {%
client.global.set("matchId", response.body.id);
%}

### List all matches (most recent first)
GET {{host}}/matches

### Get a specific match
GET {{host}}/matches/{{matchId}}

### All matches involving FC Tecnocampus
GET {{host}}/teams/{{teamId}}/matches

### Top 10 scorers
GET {{host}}/players/top-scorers


# =============================================================================
# 5. TRANSFERS & RELEASES
# =============================================================================

### Transfer the forward from FC Tecnocampus to Real Mataró (fee = skill × 3)
POST {{host}}/teams/{{teamId}}/transfer/{{forwardId}}/to/{{rivalTeamId}}

### Release the midfielder back into the free-agent pool (refund = skill)
POST {{host}}/teams/{{teamId}}/release/{{midId}}


# =============================================================================
# 6. RECOVER FROM INJURY
# =============================================================================
# Injuries are random (10% per side per match). After enough matches, a player
# may end up with status INJURED — only then will recover succeed (otherwise 400).

### Recover a player (will return 400 unless they're currently INJURED)
POST {{host}}/players/{{defId}}/recover


# =============================================================================
# 7. CLEANUP
# =============================================================================

### Delete a single player (also removed from any team's roster)
DELETE {{host}}/players/{{midId}}

### Delete a team (every remaining player becomes FREE_AGENT)
DELETE {{host}}/teams/{{teamId}}


# =============================================================================
# 8. ERROR / VALIDATION CHECKS — these should NOT return 2xx
# =============================================================================

### 400 — Player name too short
POST {{host}}/players
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "X",
  "position": "FWD",
  "skillLevel": 50
}

### 400 — Player skillLevel out of range
POST {{host}}/players
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test Player",
  "position": "FWD",
  "skillLevel": 150
}

### 400 — Invalid position
POST {{host}}/players
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test Player",
  "position": "STRIKER",
  "skillLevel": 50
}

### 400 — Team name too short
POST {{host}}/teams
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "FC",
  "city": "Mataró"
}

### 400 — Empty city
POST {{host}}/teams
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Valid Team Name",
  "city": ""
}

### 409 — Duplicate team name (case-insensitive)
POST {{host}}/teams
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "real mataró",
  "city": "Other City"
}

### 400 — A team cannot play against itself
POST {{host}}/matches
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "homeTeamId": "{{rivalTeamId}}",
  "awayTeamId": "{{rivalTeamId}}"
}

### 404 — Player not found
GET {{host}}/players/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

### 404 — Team not found
GET {{host}}/teams/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

### 404 — Match not found
GET {{host}}/matches/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
